{
  "stem": "27507.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And although they kept the tradition in so far that they were celebrating the holidays-- Jewish holidays-- and so on, they had not otherwise any traditional leanings.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "My family from my mother's side was very different, because that was much more traditional Jewish family, came from Kalisz in Western Poland.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And there was a really big family of 12 children, my mother among them.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Five brothers and seven sisters.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And the parents were orthodox, particularly the father was orthodox.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "He was Hasid, and he belonged to the Hasidim here.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I always remember him in a more or less traditional Jewish clothes, in kind of a long black coat or-- and rather and-- with a long beard.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And the whole house was-- and he was, of course, completely orthodox, although to me he had to speak Polish because he couldn't speak to me Yiddish, as he spoke to his wife.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But all of the children were--",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Because I didn't speak Yiddish, that's right.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But all the children were-- apart from the maybe two oldest-- all of them didn't want to remain traditional, and they more or less rebelled.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they always wanted to study in the first place.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And indeed of my-- of the brothers and sisters of my mother, most of them went to university, to higher education.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And most of them basically rebelled against the traditional background and wanted to become-- to be part of the more modern society.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Right.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So we were living-- I spent all my first six years of my life in Warsaw in this apartment in Alberta, which was very comfortable, although I and-- apart from my parents and myself, there was-- there were-- there was a maid and nanny who was looking after me.",
      "word_count": 49
    }
  ],
